<emphasis box="[439,633,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Patrera bonaldoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[641,705,691,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[641,705,691,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be recognized by having both branches of retrolateral tibial apophysis short and truncated, by the laminar-shaped, very long embolus with filiform apex and by the membranous ventral tegular process (
<figureCitation box="[416,493,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
C–E). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[867,1001,763,789]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[867,1001,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1068,763,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1007,1068,763,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the epigynal plate with lateral border curved in the anterior region (
<figureCitation box="[560,638,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,181,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-18@31.[151,1435,181,1700]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15A–G. Patrera carvalhoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10615):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-10631): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C: 0.8; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468415/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
F–G), but differs by the long and thick hood (triangular in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1286,1420,799,825]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[1286,1420,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), thin and sinuous copulatory ducts (wide in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[631,765,835,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[631,765,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and oval spermathecae (bean-shaped in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1232,1366,835,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[1232,1366,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,907,933]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[353,419,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male.</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[435,544,907,933]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-9661). Carapace brownish, darker on the cephalic region (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1424,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae dark brown. Labium and endites brown. Sternum yellowish. Legs yellow, darkest from tibiae to tarsi. Abdomen dorsally grayish; ventrally yellow (
<figureCitation box="[660,764,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets yellow. Total length 6.76, carapace length 3.27, width 2.41, high 0.84. Clypeus height 0.12. Eye diameters and interdistances:AME 0.13, ALE 0.15, PME 0.15, PLE 0.15; AME–AME 0.29, AME–ALE 0.31, PME–PME 0.46, PME–PLE 0.42, ALE–PLE 0.45. Chelicerae 1.4 long, four promarginal teeth; six retromarginal denticles. Leg measurements: leg I—femur 3.07/ patella 1.27/ tibia 3.29/ metatarsus 2.24/ tarsus 0.71/ total 10.58; II—2.77/ 1.22/ 2.94/ 2.14/ 0.91/ 9.98; III—1.98/ 0.82/ 1.38/ 1.69/ 0.62/ 6.49; IV—2.67/ 1.15/ 2.3/ 2.5/ 0.77/ 9.39. Leg spination: I—metatarsus v2-0-1, p1-1-0, r0-1-0; II—tibia r1-1-0, metatarsus v2-0-1, p1-1-0, r0-1-0; III—tibia d1-0-0, v1-2-2, p1-1-1, r1-1-1, metatarsus p1-2-2, r1-1-2; IV—tibia d1- 0-0, p0-1-1, metatarsus d0-1-0, v2-2-1, p1-2-2, r1-1-2. Abdomen: length 3.25, epigastric furrow 0.94 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.38 from base of spinnerets. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis bifid, short and with both branches apically truncated, dorsal branch wider than the ventral one; cymbium twice longer than tibia; subtegulum longer than wide, thin, with the distal projection inconspicuous; tegulum longer than wide with a membranous and laminar distal projection; median apophysis very short, apically situated; embolus long, laminar, apically filiform with narrow base and basally inserted on the tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[671,750,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
C–E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[298,401,1447,1473]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Paratype</typeStatus>
, AMNH). Carapace and cephalic region yellow (
<figureCitation box="[948,1051,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae yellow. Labium, sternum and endites yellow. Abdomen grey (
<figureCitation box="[613,716,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets yellow. Total length 5.9, carapace length 2.6, width 1.9. Clypeus height 0.08. Eye diameters and interdistances:AME 0.08, ALE 0.10, PME 0.10, PLE 0.10; AME–AME 0.04, AME–ALE 0.06, PME–PME 0.18, PME–PLE 0.12, ALE–PLE 0.08. Chelicerae 1.0 long, four promarginal teeth; five retromarginal denticles. Leg measurements: Leg I—femur 2.0/ patella 1.0/ tibia 1.72/ metatarsus 1.33/ tarsus 0.7/ total 6.75; II—1.8/ 0.9/ 1.7/ 1.34/ 0.6/ 6.34; III—1.5/ 0.7/ 1.0/ 1.2/ 0.5/ 4.9; IV—2.0/ 0.8/ 1.2/ 2.1/ 0.64/ 6.74. Leg spination: I—p1-0-0; II—tibia v2-2-0, p0-0-1; III—tibia v1-2-2, p1v-0-1-1, r0-1-1; IV—tibia v2-2-2, p1- 1-1, r1-1-1, metatarsus v2-2-2, p1-1-1, r1-1-1. Abdomen: length 3.2, epigastric furrow 0.8 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.0 from base of spinnerets. Epigynum: hood large, wide and posteriorly projected; lateral borders sclerotized, thin, semicircular and extended over the epigynal atrium; atrium extremely short; internally with copulatory ducts long and thin; seminal receptacles small, rounded and anteriorly situated on the copulatory ducts; spermathecae large, oval with an anterior extension and posteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts shorter than spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[160,238,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[151,1435,181,1771]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13A–D. Patrera bonaldoi n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-9661): A habitus, C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (AMNH): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: BE, base of the embolus; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 3.5mm; C: 1mm; D–E: 0.5mm; F–G: 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468409/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1358,1915,1942]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1915,1941]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Variation.</emphasis>
Males (n=8): total length: 5.70–6.76; carapace length: 3.00–3.45; femur I length: 2.36–3.01.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,1951,1977]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Natural History.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[459,507,1952,1978]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected beating low shrubs, in a conserved high mountain wet forest ecosystem, together with the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[703,802,1987,2013]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florezi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[703,802,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. florezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[808,871,1987,2013]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[808,871,1987,2013]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, at an elevation between 
<quantity box="[1156,1307,1987,2014]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3465" metricValueMax="5.13" metricValueMin="1.563" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="3346.5" valueMax="5130.0" valueMin="1563.0">1563–5130m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,937,150,177]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[199,937,150,177]" box="[199,937,150,177]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
